{
  "stem": "1858.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 289.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know, if a girl would break down in the middle of the night and it seemed like she no longer cares or can go on, the rest of the girls would come and sit with her and talk to her just to help her make through that one more night, always hoping that perhaps tomorrow things will look better, that perhaps tomorrow this will end.",
      "word_count": 66
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We always looked for the future, for tomorrow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Had we known-- had I known, in 1943, in August, that I would live in the concentration camp for two years, I think I would have given up a long time before.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was always that tomorrow, things will change.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We didn't look far ahead into the future, only until tomorrow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You know, many times when a girl was so sad and everybody was crying, somebody would start singing.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And often, it was my sister Tola, who sang so beautiful, would start singing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because song has a means of expressing sorrow, pain, but also hope, courage.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And it was often that when our spirit sank, when we felt at the lowest point in our life, that suddenly somebody would start.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the rest of us often would join in a song.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, our state of our mental life was reduced to the lowest possible level.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I haven't seen a written material for so many years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I haven't been so cut off from the rest of the world physically as well as mentally.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What did it do to a human brain?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But somehow, or maybe in spite of everything, we managed to preserve the vestiges of our spiritual freedom of mind.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, religion was a very important part of our lives.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
